tios of some galaxies being offset by enhanced H$\\alpha$\nfrom the brightest and high mass galaxy populations. Our findings confirm the\nnecessity to fully sample the HI mass range for a complete census of local star\nformation to include lower stellar mass galaxies which dominate the local\nUniverse.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 15 Jun 2018 09:46:32 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-06-27"}
